                <head>No. 28.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Earl <persName type="from">Granville</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-03-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 7, 1882</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your letter of the 24th ultimo, forwarding a copy of a resolution of the United
                    States House of Representatives, calling for information concerning the arrest
                    and imprisonment of American citizens by the British Government.</p>
                <p>In reply, I beg leave to acquaint you that this matter has been referred to the
                    proper department of Her Majesty’s Government.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GRANVILLE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
